cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a new dataset for benchmarking out-of-distribution robustness in computer vision, specifically for the MNIST test set. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of state-of-the-art computer vision models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of model-agnostic corruptions, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions adversarial defenses, which could suggest a potential fit for cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the hope that the benchmark will be useful for future work in designing systems that are able to learn robust feature representations, which could suggest a potential fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
